    • Constructor Detail

      • CSVRecord

        public CSVRecord(Class<T> fields)
        Deprecated. 
        Constructs a new CSVRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the fields parameter. The record way is RecordWay.IN. The lenght of this record is calculated with the sum of the lenght of every field. The value of every field is initialized with a default value (if present) Every value is separated with the CSVSep.COMMA. The fields aren't enclosing, eccept they contain the char CSVSep.COMMA. The enclosing char is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE. Each of the embedded CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE characters is represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Parameters:
        fields - the fields of this Record

      • CSVRecord

        public CSVRecord(RecordWay recordWay,
                 String csvRecord,
                 Class<T> fields,
                 List<FieldExtendedProperty> fieldExtendedProperties)
        Deprecated. 
        Constructs a new CSVRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the fields parameter. The record way is initialized with the value of the recordWay parameter. The value of every field is initialized with the formatted value present in the relative position of the csvRecord parameter. To every field of the record are applied the extended properties present in the fieldExtendedProperties parameter. Only the following properties are permitted at record level:
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.LPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.RPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.VALIDATOR
        Every value is separated with the CSVSep.COMMA. The fields aren't enclosing, eccept they contain the char CSVSep.COMMA. The enclosing char is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE. Each of the embedded CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE characters is represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Parameters:
        recordWay - the way of this record
        csvRecord - the formatted string of this Record
        fields - the fields of this Record
        fieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of field applied to every fields of the record

      • CSVRecord

        public CSVRecord(RecordWay recordWay,
                 String csvRecord,
                 Class<T> fields,
                 List<FieldExtendedProperty> fieldExtendedProperties,
                 CSVSep recordSep,
                 String recordOtherSep,
                 CSVEnc recordEnclosing,
                 boolean recordEncloseAllFields)
        Deprecated. 
        Constructs a new CSVRecord that represents the CSV fields indicated by the fields parameter. The record way is initialized with the value of the recordWay parameter. The value of every field is initialized with the formatted value present in the relative position of the csvRecord parameter. To every field of the record are applied the extended properties present in the fieldExtendedProperties parameter. Only the following properties are permitted at record level:
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.LPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.RPAD
        • FieldExtendedPropertyType.VALIDATOR
        Every value is separated with the recordSep param. If the recordSep param is null, the default sep is CSVSep.COMMA. If recordEncloseAllFields is true, every field of the record is enclosed with the recordEnclosing param. If the recordEnclosing param is null, the default enclosing is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE. If the recordEncloseAllFields param is false the fields aren't enclosing, eccept they contain the char sep. Each of the embedded char enclosing characters is represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Parameters:
        recordWay - the way of this record
        csvRecord - the formatted string of this Record
        fields - the fields of this Record
        fieldExtendedProperties - the extended properties of field applied to every fields of the record
        recordSep - the field separator. If null the sep is CSVSep.COMMA
        recordOtherSep - the field separator if sep param is CSVSep.OTHER. Size must be eq 1. If null the default sep is CSVSep.COMMA
        recordEnclosing - the enclosing char. If null the enclosing char is CSVEnc.DOUBLE_QUOTE
        recordEncloseAllFields - if true every field of the record is enclosed with the enclosing char, otherwise only field which contains sep

      • toString

        public String toString()
                throws RecordException
        Deprecated. 
        Returns a CSV String object representing this record. The returned string is composed with the formatted unpadded value of every field of this record. Every value is separated with the CSVSep defined for this CSV record. If encloseAllFields defined for this CSV record is true, every field of the record is enclosed with the enclosing defined for this CSV record. If the encloseAllFields is false the fields aren't enclosing, eccept they contain the char sep. Each of the embedded char enclosing characters is represented by a pair of double-enclosing characters.
        Overrides:
        toString in class AbstractRecord
        Returns:
        a CSV string representation of this record
        Throws:
        RecordException - it the status of this record is ERROR
